title.narrative: OUTPUT 6.2 - CP SERVICES

description.narrative: By 2024, accessible and quality birth registration and child protection (prevention and response) services are in place and delivered by qualified statutory and non statutory service providers in most disadvantaged localities in Liberia., which contributes to Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, boys and girls In Liberia have access to quality prevention and response services for violence, abuse and exploitation and for birth registration.

title.narrative: By 2024, accessible and quality birth registration and child protection (prevention and response) services are in place anddelivered by qualified statutory and non statutory service providers in most disadvantaged localities in Liberia.

description.narrative: At least 293,431 children, adolescents and their parents/caregivers directly benefited from multifaceted child protection services delivered at various delivery points, including 332 health centres, 50 schools, 16 adolescent/youth resource centres, etc. Services include community-based psychosocial support (PSS) and case management, diversion and non-custodial measures, BR and certification, life skills trainings, trainings in technical and vocational skills, parenting skills trainings, buddy clubs and adolescent peer educator support services. At 257,132, BR exceeded the annual target of 220,000, representing 117% achievement status. To date, 98% of districts in Liberia have access to free and universal BR services | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
